<div id="banner">
	<h1>Screen Savers on the Desktop</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>Pat Jensen <a href="http://apple.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=38678&cid=4141399">has posted a cool trick for running your screen saver on your desktop</a>. Just open a terminal, and type:</p></p>

<p><code>/System/Library/Frameworks/ScreenSaver.framework/Resources/ScreenSaverEngine.app/Contents/MacOS/ScreenSaverEngine -background</code></p>

<p>Neat. Bill Bumgarner points out that if you replace <code>background</code> with <code>foreground</code> you can see them in the foreground too. He has a prefPanel, <a href="http://www.versiontracker.com/moreinfo.fcgi?id=15965&db=macosx">FackBore</a> that lets you configure all this.</p>

<p class="posted">posted August 26, 2002 09:07 PM (<a class="category" href="cat_technology">Technology</a>)  <a href="000528" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

